{
  "texts": [
    "Both in the TG and the CG the audience demand is perceived as the most persuasive features; presentational devices are, instead, considered by far the least persuasive by the CG while this is not the case for the TG.",
    "This confirms the engaging role played by language in a conversational, rather than written format which creates a feeling of reciprocation and mutual understanding not achievable through tweets and Facebook posts.",
    "The latter might be tailored towards an audience with respect to whom the speaker does not feel included.",
    "Turning to question 4, the most apparent result is that the TG recognised a larger number of rhetorical strategies (91) compared to the CG (73).",
    "This result was expected since the main goal of Botlitica is that of streamlining the process of information retrieval customised by the journalist more flexibly, compared to standard query tools based, for example, on keywords' search."
  ]
}